<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 04 at 2:37PM EDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Cherokee and
western Clay Counties through 315 PM EDT...
At 236 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hayesville, moving west at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hayesville, Marble and Brasstown.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
